take the room at the end of

266
00:31:58,767 --> 00:32:02,726
the corridor in your possession."

268
00:32:22,087 --> 00:32:24,920
I can tidy it up a bit...

269
00:32:33,287 --> 00:32:37,678
Why is this bathrobe here?
Is it a right place for it?

270
00:32:41,927 --> 00:32:45,886
- What's this letter?
- It's from mom.

271
00:32:45,927 --> 00:32:50,045
- What are you waiting for then?
- I'd have told you.

272
00:32:50,087 --> 00:32:54,046
- What does she write?
- She says she's fine.

273
00:32:54,087 --> 00:32:58,717
She hasn't called to avoid a fight.
She is still in Venice.

274
00:32:58,807 --> 00:33:02,766
"... so I thought I'd take 
a short vacation.

275
00:33:02,807 --> 00:33:07,278
After all everyone gets a time off.
I've found a job."

276
00:33:07,327 --> 00:33:12,276
Is she on vacation or working?
I mean, we go away every year.

277
00:33:13,167 --> 00:33:18,036
"P.S.: Please can you care for the 
plants on the kitchen's balcony

278
00:33:18,127 --> 00:33:22,245
every 2. day? Especially the
mint dries up quickly."

279
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:27,160
Which one is the mint?
Salvo!

280
00:33:27,647 --> 00:33:30,639
- Is this mint?
- Yes.

281
00:33:30,687 --> 00:33:33,042
Hold it.

282
00:33:33,087 --> 00:33:36,284
- Papa, what are you doing...
- It sure won't dry up now!

283
00:33:36,327 --> 00:33:38,761
Cut it out.

284
00:33:38,807 --> 00:33:42,766
Hey honey, just a second.

285
00:33:42,807 --> 00:33:45,799
- Where are you going?
- To Cinzia's.

286
00:33:45,847 --> 00:33:48,759
- Having dinner there?
- Yes. Ciao.

287
00:33:48,807 --> 00:33:53,039
- When will you be back?
- I don't know. Later.

288
00:33:57,887 --> 00:34:02,039
- You're not eating?
- I'm not hungry.

289
00:34:03,887 --> 00:34:07,277
Did you read your mom's letter?

290
00:34:07,327 --> 00:34:11,286
- Do you think it's normal?
- How should I know?

292
00:34:16,447 --> 00:34:20,281
Hi Mama! I was on my way over.
Alba wrote again.

293
00:34:20,327 --> 00:34:23,842
- What mouthwash do you use?
- I don't.

294
00:34:23,887 --> 00:34:26,879
- What does she say?
- She's on vacation.

295
00:34:26,927 --> 00:34:30,886
She'll be back soon. She said 
she'd lend me her travel drier.

296
00:34:30,927 --> 00:34:33,919
- It's in the bathroom I guess?
- Where are you going?

297
00:34:33,967 --> 00:34:38,518
That cruise I won, to the Fjords.
Here it is. Cute!

298
00:34:38,567 --> 00:34:41,639
- When do you go?
- In 2 days.

299
00:34:41,687 --> 00:34:45,726
Honey, try to drop by, if you can.
The washing machine door is stuck.

300
00:34:45,767 --> 00:34:50,079
- Have you eaten?
- No, I'm dieting. Nothing fits.

301
00:34:52,927 --> 00:34:55,077
Mimmo...

302
00:34:57,567 --> 00:35:01,560
Can we meet a bit later on Thursday?

303
00:35:01,607 --> 00:35:05,600
- I have to take Samy to the dentist.
- Ketty, I'm desperate.

304
00:35:05,647 --> 00:35:09,401
The coffeemachine blew up yesterday.

305
00:35:09,447 --> 00:35:13,679
- And what should I tell the neighbors?
- Say she's on vacation.

306
00:35:15,767 --> 00:35:19,282
Could you iron a few shirts for me?

307
00:35:19,327 --> 00:35:23,798
Mimmo, are you crazy? 
I'm your mistress, not your wife! 

308
00:35:23,847 --> 00:35:28,079
- Okay, but after 5 years...
- I hope Rosy's back soon.

309
00:35:30,087 --> 00:35:33,238
Come on, move it!

310
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:40,683
You think it's normal,
somebody just goes like that?

311
00:35:41,607 --> 00:35:46,078
Can't we do anything from the 
legal point of view?

312
00:35:46,207 --> 00:35:51,076
The last thing I need is a private 
eye bleeding me dry!

313
00:35:51,127 --> 00:35:55,086
Good idea, great!
We need more counselors like you.

314
00:35:55,607 --> 00:35:59,680
Thanks a lot. Ciao. Ciao!

316
00:36:07,887 --> 00:36:12,358
Mimmo? I go to that kindergarten 
to Civitella.

317
00:36:12,407 --> 00:36:16,400
The plumber, Di Matteo sent is here.

318
00:36:16,447 --> 00:36:19,564
Can you deal with him?

319
00:36:19,607 --> 00:36:23,043
Ah, any news?

320
00:36:23,087 --> 00:36:27,046
When I get any news, you'll be 
the first who knows, all right?

321
00:36:27,087 --> 00:36:29,078
All right.

322
00:36:34,167 --> 00:36:38,080
"Costantino Caponangeli...."
Nice name.

323
00:36:38,687 --> 00:36:43,078
"Plumber and shutter fitter.

324
00:36:43,687 --> 00:36:47,680
Intern with the MGCF..." What's that?

325
00:36:47,807 --> 00:36:51,925
The Municipal Gas Company of Foggia.

326
00:36:51,967 --> 00:36:55,926
A sportsman, I see...
"Third place in the

327
00:36:55,967 --> 00:37:00,245
regional darts tournament."
You've put your hobbies too.

328
00:37:01,087 --> 00:37:03,237
"Reading detective stories."

329
00:37:08,167 --> 00:37:10,158
How come?

330
00:37:11,607 --> 00:37:15,919
- I... I love them.
- How many have you read?

331
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:20,677
- I'd have to check...
- Off the top of your head.

332
00:37:21,287 --> 00:37:24,279
285... and a half.

333
00:37:24,327 --> 00:37:28,286
Holy shit!

334
00:37:31,807 --> 00:37:34,446
- Are you married?
- No.

335
00:37:34,487 --> 00:37:38,116
- Engaged?
- No.

336
00:37:38,167 --> 00:37:42,160
- Willing to relocate?
- Yes, where?

337
00:37:42,247 --> 00:37:46,684
Venice. Ever been there?

338
00:37:55,527 --> 00:37:58,087
My wife.

339
00:38:00,127 --> 00:38:04,166
I'm out of saran wrap, 
but look what I did:

340
00:38:04,207 --> 00:38:08,678
O for omelet, C for cheese, M for
mortadella. If you want one with 

341
00:38:08,767 --> 00:38:12,680
- Milan Salami I'll put an MS..
- Mama, I'm going to Venice,

342
00:38:12,767 --> 00:38:17,283
- not for camping in Alps.
- How long will this last?

343
00:38:17,327 --> 00:38:21,923
10 days or so, I already told you.
Anyways, I've got the mobile.

344
00:38:21,967 --> 00:38:26,279
I can only call Mr. Barletta,
but you can call me anytime.

345
00:38:26,647 --> 00:38:30,879
This is a steady job!
1.700.000 lire plus benefits.

346
00:38:31,327 --> 00:38:34,319
But why Venice?

347
00:38:34,367 --> 00:38:38,679
It's a city with enormous problems.
They even called a Dutch engineer.

348
00:38:38,727 --> 00:38:42,606
- I'll miss my train...
- Have you got your asthma spray?

349
00:38:42,647 --> 00:38:45,639
- Yes.
- Is your money in your socks?

350
00:38:45,687 --> 00:38:48,645
You want me to miss the train?

351
00:38:48,727 --> 00:38:52,276
At least say good bye to Silvia.

352
00:38:52,327 --> 00:38:59,278
- We're not engaged...
- Go on Tino!

353
00:39:01,447 --> 00:39:05,679
- Ciao, Mama.
- Have a good trip, son.

354
00:39:06,007 --> 00:39:09,283
Take care!

359
00:39:50,127 --> 00:39:54,086
Hello? Good evening, Mr. Barletta.

360
00:39:54,127 --> 00:39:58,518
No, I don't have a room yet. 
I just got here. Yes!

361
00:39:58,567 --> 00:40:03,482
On the train, I drew up an action 
plan. It won't take me long.

362
00:40:03,527 --> 00:40:07,520
Yes. Good bye. Good-bye Mr. Barletta.

363
00:40:07,567 --> 00:40:11,685
Excuse me, I wouldn't be so 
sure, if I were you.

364
00:40:12,247 --> 00:40:16,035
- What did you say?
- First time in Venice?

365
00:40:16,087 --> 00:40:19,875
- Yes, why?
- Nothing to get until September.

366
00:40:19,927 --> 00:40:24,079
- How do you know?
- I'm in that business. For years.

367
00:40:24,207 --> 00:40:27,597
Look, you see this queue?

368
00:40:28,007 --> 00:40:30,043
- So?
- So?

369
00:40:30,087 --> 00:40:34,239
What do you think these people 
are lined up for?

370
00:40:34,327 --> 00:40:38,286
They want a room too.

371
00:40:41,207 --> 00:40:45,086
- They're hard to find?
- You don't believe me?

372
00:40:45,207 --> 00:40:49,246
Here, make a call!
How much can you pay?

373
00:40:49,927 --> 00:40:53,886
Not more then 50.000 a day.

374
00:40:54,287 --> 00:40:58,565
- 50.000 lire a day? In Venice?
- That's all I can pay, 50.000.

375
00:40:58,607 --> 00:41:01,599
Maybe I have what you need.

377
00:41:30,087 --> 00:41:33,079
Welcome, Sir!

378
00:41:33,287 --> 00:41:34,925
Welcome?

379
00:41:34,967 --> 00:41:37,959
I take your suitcase.

380
00:41:38,007 --> 00:41:42,000
You find the way easy?
Boss explained it good?

381
00:41:42,047 --> 00:41:45,039
Map of the city,

382
00:41:45,087 --> 00:41:46,645
room-key, minibar

383
00:41:46,687 --> 00:41:49,520
and TV.

384
00:41:49,567 --> 00:41:52,798
If you getting problems...

385
00:41:52,847 --> 00:41:55,998
This is my phone number!

386
00:41:56,567 --> 00:42:00,560
Bring with you who you like,
all inclusive.

387
00:42:00,607 --> 00:42:03,599
One week advance,

388
00:42:03,647 --> 00:42:08,641
- 350.000 cash in hand.
- But this isn't a hotel.

389
00:42:09,767 --> 00:42:13,760
You change mind? No problemo.
You look for other hotel!

390
00:42:16,607 --> 00:42:18,404
Wait!

391
00:42:18,447 --> 00:42:21,245
Is breakfast included?

393
00:42:34,727 --> 00:42:38,276
- I got everything, even ginger.
- Ginger?

394
00:42:38,327 --> 00:42:41,319
- Don't you use it?
_ No.

395
00:42:41,367 --> 00:42:45,326
- Got a client?
- A tax accountant.

396
00:42:45,367 --> 00:42:49,326
He had a special one and 
sleeps now like a baby.

397
00:42:49,367 --> 00:42:53,918
- What's that in there?
- I got an advance.

398
00:42:53,967 --> 00:42:58,006
- Knock when you're done.
- Okay, ciao.

401
00:44:47,487 --> 00:44:52,003
Hallo? Pension Canaletto? I'd like 
to speak to Mrs. Rosalba Barletta.

402
00:44:53,887 --> 00:44:57,880
She is not staying with you?
Strange, she left me this number.

403
00:44:57,967 --> 00:45:02,279
Maybe she checked in as Maresanto?
Okay, thank you...

404
00:45:02,527 --> 00:45:06,600
Wait! Do you have any rooms?

405
00:45:06,647 --> 00:45:10,879
Nothing before September...
Thank you. Good bye.

408
00:45:33,287 --> 00:45:35,676
Yes?

409
00:45:35,727 --> 00:45:38,878
Hi, mom. Yes.

410
00:45:39,887 --> 00:45:43,880
I just got back to the hotel.

412
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:20,885
- Good night.
- Good night to you.

414
00:46:34,967 --> 00:46:37,959
- Rosalba, you must help me.
- Me?

415
00:46:38,007 --> 00:46:42,080
I want to adopt a boy.
Give me a quick mothership lesson.

416
00:46:42,847 --> 00:46:45,839
Mothership lesson?

417
00:46:45,887 --> 00:46:49,880
I never understood a thing 
about motherhood.

418
00:46:49,927 --> 00:46:52,885
Help me, please..

419
00:46:52,967 --> 00:46:56,926
- How old is the boy?
- Want to see him?

420
00:46:56,967 --> 00:46:59,606
Come on.

421
00:46:59,647 --> 00:47:01,478
Nic!

422
00:47:01,527 --> 00:47:05,884
Hi, mom. Have you seen my camera?

423
00:47:06,327 --> 00:47:10,036
- I put it in the drawer.
- Do you like it?

424
00:47:10,087 --> 00:47:14,080
She's on a 3 Days Trial.
I hope it works out this time.

425
00:47:14,127 --> 00:47:18,245
- Have you tried others?
- Loads.

426
00:47:18,607 --> 00:47:22,282
Even one called Vera Zasulic, 
but she was useless

427
00:47:28,487 --> 00:47:30,876
Vera...

428
00:47:32,127 --> 00:47:34,277
Vera!

429
00:47:34,327 --> 00:47:38,366
The water's boiling.

430
00:47:38,407 --> 00:47:43,276
I don't have time now,
have to finish by 6.

431
00:47:43,327 --> 00:47:46,364
- They can come back later.
- No, I promised it would be ready.

432
00:47:46,407 --> 00:47:50,366
Beautyful things take time..

433
00:47:50,407 --> 00:47:54,366
Come and have your tea.

434
00:47:55,207 --> 00:47:59,564
Fermo, I'm sorry, but I hate 
to make people wait..

435
00:47:59,607 --> 00:48:03,600
You're wrong. The people have 
to learn to wait.

436
00:48:06,287 --> 00:48:10,280
What were you saying about 
the tulips before?

437
00:48:10,327 --> 00:48:14,479
Concerning tulips, contrary to 
what people think, they aren't 

438
00:48:14,527 --> 00:48:18,679
from Holland, but from Persia. The
"Arabian Nights" are full of tulips.

439
00:48:20,287 --> 00:48:24,360
Even the "Trio Lescana" knew that.
What did they sing again...

440
00:48:24,687 --> 00:48:27,679
"Tuli-Tuli-Tulipani..."

441
00:48:27,727 --> 00:48:32,084
See, you know it too. 

442
00:48:32,287 --> 00:48:37,077
I'll go. No, pour the tea. 
Sit down.

443
00:48:37,127 --> 00:48:40,119
- Hello, have you made your choice?
- Yes, I'd like some Irises.

444
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:44,240
Are you a monarchist by any chance?
They were Loui's VII's emblem.

445
00:48:44,567 --> 00:48:48,526
- Are they a gift?
- Yes, for a wedding anniversary.

446
00:48:48,567 --> 00:48:52,037
Take some narcissuses or lilies then.

447
00:48:52,087 --> 00:48:56,239
Yes, but you've got irises over there.

448
00:48:57,807 --> 00:49:02,278
You take me for a mere merchant?
Are flowers here are just to suit us?

449
00:49:02,327 --> 00:49:06,286
What have irises got to do with 
anniversaries?

450
00:49:06,327 --> 00:49:10,525
"Iridacea", to call them by 
their true name.

451
00:49:10,567 --> 00:49:13,559
- Can you explain?
- I was wrong.

452
00:49:13,607 --> 00:49:17,839
Everyone's is going crazy.

453
00:49:17,887 --> 00:49:22,244
Ah, my dear, there is no more
humility in the world.

454
00:49:25,007 --> 00:49:27,999
My grandpa ate garlic too.

455
00:49:28,047 --> 00:49:32,245
- Was he an anarchist too ?
- I don't think so.

456
00:49:33,287 --> 00:49:38,281
In my family are all anarchists
and everyone has heart problems.

457
00:49:39,247 --> 00:49:43,240
- Shall we drink our tea?
- All right.

458
00:49:45,407 --> 00:49:49,400
I found him once doubled up 
on the doormat.

459
00:49:49,447 --> 00:49:53,440
- What had happened to him?
- Nothing.

460
00:49:53,487 --> 00:49:57,446
A sciatic attack. I fixed him up.

461
00:49:59,007 --> 00:50:03,239
Any idea, where he goes every
morning at 7.30?

462
00:50:03,487 --> 00:50:06,684
I don't know. Fernando is a 
mystery to me.

463
00:50:06,727 --> 00:50:10,686
When he writes all his "P"s 
and "T"s are really long.

464
00:50:11,367 --> 00:50:15,360
He must be a very passionate man.

465
00:50:15,407 --> 00:50:19,798
The woman who cleans the stairs 
says he has a son.

466
00:50:19,847 --> 00:50:23,965
- A son?
- I don't know. She talks rubbish.

467
00:50:24,367 --> 00:50:27,677
Relax now...

468
00:50:33,647 --> 00:50:37,686
I was forgetting my doubts and 
scruples. Only she counted for me.

469
00:50:38,447 --> 00:50:42,884
I remember you being taller 
and gentler.

470
00:50:42,927 --> 00:50:46,886
- You missed me?
- Like a blind misses his eyes...

471
00:50:46,927 --> 00:50:49,885
Oh gosh... Do you think

472
00:50:49,967 --> 00:50:54,245
they really used to talk like that?

473
00:50:54,287 --> 00:50:58,439
Now they say, they want to 
do it under the table

474
00:50:58,487 --> 00:51:02,878
or hanging in chains on some pipes.

475
00:51:03,287 --> 00:51:06,518
- Sit down.
- No, Roger...

476
00:51:06,567 --> 00:51:10,879
- Careful, my earrings...
- Want to be dried, yes or no??

479
00:51:36,007 --> 00:51:38,077
Good evening.

480
00:51:38,327 --> 00:51:40,318
Good evening.

481
00:51:40,367 --> 00:51:44,326
"Good night" is more appropriate.

482
00:51:44,367 --> 00:51:48,326
I was at Grazia's.
We fell asleep on the couch.

483
00:51:48,367 --> 00:51:53,316
I'd be lying, if I said, I 
hadn't noticed your absence.

484
00:51:59,647 --> 00:52:02,684
You're not feeling well?

485
00:52:02,727 --> 00:52:07,243
Without her appendix, I fear that
our cook isn't the same woman.

486
00:52:09,327 --> 00:52:13,878
Luckily, I've never had stomach 
problems.

487
00:52:14,167 --> 00:52:17,159
I'm delighted.

488
00:52:17,207 --> 00:52:20,756
Are you a musician?

489
00:52:23,007 --> 00:52:27,000
I saw the accordion in the closet.

490
00:52:27,047 --> 00:52:31,086
I was looking for a mirror.
I'm sorry.

491
00:52:32,527 --> 00:52:36,566
It was a payment for a gambling 
debt, I just never sold it.

492
00:52:36,607 --> 00:52:41,317
Should I infer that you're 
capable of playing it?

493
00:52:41,607 --> 00:52:46,044
When I was 12 my granddad taught 
me as little. Then he

494
00:52:46,087 --> 00:52:49,079
fell off an unfinished bridge.

495
00:52:49,127 --> 00:52:53,245
Your grandfather devoted himself 
to building bridges?

496
00:52:53,487 --> 00:52:58,083
No, one night he was cycling home
and thought the bridge was finished.

497
00:53:00,407 --> 00:53:04,480
Sometimes, distraction can be fatal.

498
00:53:05,887 --> 00:53:08,082
You're telling me.

499
00:53:20,887 --> 00:53:25,199
"In amongst all of my bits and pieces
I found these old records.

500
00:53:25,247 --> 00:53:28,284
I think, they might help you,

501
00:53:28,327 --> 00:53:32,286
to reacquire the familiarity 
with the instrument."

503
00:53:39,807 --> 00:53:43,083
I'm sorry. I don't know her.

508
00:55:25,967 --> 00:55:30,961
Yes? Good evening, Mr. Barletta.
No. No great news today either.

509
00:55:32,087 --> 00:55:35,159
7 hardwarestores, 3 hairdressers...

510
00:55:35,207 --> 00:55:39,246
I got enough of your lists, 
Caponangeli!

511
00:55:39,487 --> 00:55:43,639
I wanted hard facts from you!
You know what that means?

512
00:55:43,687 --> 00:55:47,646
- So what's the delay?
- I went to the VGS...

513
00:55:47,687 --> 00:55:50,679
- Venice Graphology Society.
- What for?

514
00:55:50,727 --> 00:55:54,686
You told me she did a 
graphology course.

515
00:55:54,727 --> 00:55:58,720
And a clerk at the haberdasher's
says, that his mother saw your

516
00:55:58,767 --> 00:56:02,726
wife yesterday by a hairdresser 
in Chioggia.

517
00:56:02,767 --> 00:56:06,726
This leads me to conclude, that 
your wife is no longer in Venice.

518
00:56:06,767 --> 00:56:11,045
This would explain why I haven't 
found her.

519
00:56:11,087 --> 00:56:14,079
This explains that you're a 
total idiot!

520
00:56:14,127 --> 00:56:18,086
I got a postcard from her sent
3 days ago from Venice!

521
00:56:18,167 --> 00:56:22,240
Yes! Despite the Italian Post!
Not of your business what it says!

522
00:56:24,287 --> 00:56:26,437
The postmark?

