01:25:52,127 --> 01:25:55,039
Tell me what?

797
01:25:57,287 --> 01:26:01,963
Look, he even mended my pipe!
Do you believe in coincidence?

798
01:26:02,007 --> 01:26:06,046
He's a plumber! That's fantastic

799
01:26:06,087 --> 01:26:10,046
- Do you know his name? 
- Vittorio! Isn't that fantastic?

800
01:26:10,407 --> 01:26:15,037
He has magic hands. When he 
touches me, I catch fire!

801
01:26:16,167 --> 01:26:19,284
Where have you put him?

802
01:26:19,327 --> 01:26:22,046
In my bed.

803
01:26:28,087 --> 01:26:31,523
Look, he's so cute.

804
01:26:31,567 --> 01:26:35,242
He's sleeping like a baby.

805
01:26:36,367 --> 01:26:41,043
- That face seems familiar.
- I know what you mean.

806
01:26:41,727 --> 01:26:45,720
I thought the same thing.
What an angel...

807
01:26:45,767 --> 01:26:48,839
- Holy mother of god! It's him!
- Psst, you'll wake him up.

808
01:26:48,887 --> 01:26:52,846
- It's him.
- Not so loud. Who?

809
01:26:52,887 --> 01:26:56,880
The detective my husband sent!

810
01:26:56,927 --> 01:27:01,045
Are you crazy? He's a friend 
of Diego. Vittorio the plumber.

811
01:27:01,087 --> 01:27:05,080
I met him today. He's following 
me. Constantin! That's his name.

812
01:27:05,127 --> 01:27:09,166
- Where are his clothes?
- What are you doing?

813
01:27:10,287 --> 01:27:13,643
Look, he had them on this morning.

814
01:27:13,687 --> 01:27:17,202
- What now?
- I'm looking for his papers.

815
01:27:17,247 --> 01:27:21,240
- No, what if he wakes up?
- He won't, he's sleeping.

816
01:27:23,287 --> 01:27:27,280
- Caponangeli, Costantino Maria.
- He told me, it was Costantin.

817
01:27:27,327 --> 01:27:30,717
Via Vittorio Alfieri Nr. 7.
Pescara.

818
01:27:30,767 --> 01:27:34,726
- Do you believe me now?
- Profession: plumber

819
01:27:34,767 --> 01:27:38,646
Oh, no, I ditched the other one.

820
01:27:38,687 --> 01:27:43,715
Mrs. Rosalba. With you on accordion, 
I could perform once more.

821
01:27:43,887 --> 01:27:46,879
- He's an impostor.
- Who?

822
01:27:46,927 --> 01:27:50,886
In Grazia's bed there's a
detective, my man has engaged.

823
01:27:50,927 --> 01:27:53,919
- But he's really a plumber.
- Oh my gosh...

825
01:28:04,607 --> 01:28:09,078
It belonged to my wife's grandfather.
It was last fired at Caporetto,

826
01:28:10,287 --> 01:28:14,519
but it has been perfectly preserved

827
01:28:14,567 --> 01:28:18,526
from the perils of rust
and the wear of time.

828
01:28:18,567 --> 01:28:23,004
If I were you, I'd avoid doing 
anything to impel me

829
01:28:23,047 --> 01:28:27,086
to demonstrate the efficiency 
of its working.

830
01:28:27,287 --> 01:28:31,883
- What did you say?
- I've always had lousy luck.

831
01:28:31,927 --> 01:28:36,079
From the start. My first kiss
was in a cemetery!

832
01:28:36,287 --> 01:28:40,121
I was fifteen. We used to go 
there to smoke Joints.

833
01:28:40,167 --> 01:28:44,160
His name was even Primo!
This must be a coincidence!

834
01:28:44,207 --> 01:28:47,199
The first one always leaves the mark.

835
01:28:47,247 --> 01:28:51,081
He dumped me overnight for a girl, 

836
01:28:51,367 --> 01:28:55,883
- who did the weather report on TV!
- He wasn't right for you.

837
01:28:55,927 --> 01:29:00,239
And Ettore? He seemed so much 
in love! We went to Greece.

838
01:29:01,127 --> 01:29:05,245
First evening I found him on the
ferry kissin a sailor from Saloniki.

839
01:29:06,527 --> 01:29:10,281
I wanted no more serious relationships.

840
01:29:10,527 --> 01:29:14,281
But then I met Corrado!
Light it up for me, please.

841
01:29:14,527 --> 01:29:17,519
Love on the first sight.

842
01:29:17,567 --> 01:29:21,560
I'd have followed him to Alaska,
but he was from Chioggia,

843
01:29:21,607 --> 01:29:25,600
so I went to Chioggia instead.
After a year I found out, that

844
01:29:25,647 --> 01:29:29,720
he had 2 women - two kids with 
one and three with the other...

845
01:29:29,767 --> 01:29:33,885
- He wasn't even a Muslim!
- You were better off without him.

846
01:29:36,527 --> 01:29:40,884
Grazia, I lied to you. I'm 
Costantino Caponangeli, plumber 

847
01:29:40,967 --> 01:29:45,245
from Pescara. Mrs. Barletta's
husband hired me as detective.

848
01:29:46,087 --> 01:29:50,239
He has a bathrom company 
and I needed work!

849
01:29:50,287 --> 01:29:54,280
It was my big chance.
Grazia, look at me.

850
01:30:01,047 --> 01:30:05,245
I spent the best moments 
of my live with you.

851
01:30:05,287 --> 01:30:09,280
I knew, you had to be somewhere
and finally I've found you.

852
01:30:09,327 --> 01:30:13,286
I know now what happiness is.

853
01:30:14,167 --> 01:30:18,206
Believe me, I beseech you.

854
01:30:18,247 --> 01:30:22,240
How can I, after what has happened?

855
01:30:23,047 --> 01:30:27,245
Hand me over my mobile phone.
It's just there.

856
01:30:30,887 --> 01:30:32,878
Thank you.

857
01:30:40,047 --> 01:30:44,006
Hello, Mr.Barletta?
No, I don't know the time.

858
01:30:44,047 --> 01:30:48,245
I was wrong, she wasn't your wife.
She doesn't work for a florist

859
01:30:48,287 --> 01:30:52,280
or play accordion for him.
Yes, I'm crazy.

860
01:30:52,327 --> 01:30:56,684
Hire someone else to do it.
Throw it away.

861
01:31:12,087 --> 01:31:16,877
One has to admit, that the last 
few hours were full of emotions.

862
01:31:19,287 --> 01:31:24,236
- May I offer you a nightcap?
- No, everything's spinning.

863
01:31:39,847 --> 01:31:42,236
Fernando.

864
01:31:43,767 --> 01:31:47,726
The last time I danced was 
nine years ago.

865
01:31:47,767 --> 01:31:51,646
- On my brother's wedding.
- I'm most honored then.

866
01:31:51,687 --> 01:31:55,646
I felt like flying.

867
01:31:56,087 --> 01:32:00,080
Me too, I felt like a phoenix
rising from its ashes.

869
01:32:07,647 --> 01:32:09,877
Good night.

870
01:32:14,527 --> 01:32:16,404
Rosalba?

871
01:32:16,447 --> 01:32:18,642
Yes?

872
01:32:26,447 --> 01:32:31,077
Sunday is Eliseo's birthday.
I'd be glad, if you joined us.

873
01:32:34,447 --> 01:32:37,086
I'd love to...

876
01:34:16,487 --> 01:34:19,081
Bravo!

879
01:34:42,527 --> 01:34:46,998
- Vera, have you brought my boots?
- I put them by the stove.

880
01:34:47,247 --> 01:34:50,603
They're not there.

881
01:34:50,647 --> 01:34:54,879
- Want me to come look?
- No, I've got them now.

883
01:34:59,087 --> 01:35:02,636
Rosi, what are you doing?
Have you lost your mind?

884
01:35:02,687 --> 01:35:04,279
Why?

885
01:35:04,327 --> 01:35:08,286
- What are you doing here?
- Moving the camellias.

886
01:35:08,327 --> 01:35:12,878
You're wrecking your family.

887
01:35:16,087 --> 01:35:19,796
- Stop it...
- You're real?

888
01:35:19,847 --> 01:35:23,840
- Whaddaya think? I'm plastic?
- The lady can't decide?

889
01:35:23,887 --> 01:35:27,880
A special occasion or an 
act of politeness?

890
01:35:27,927 --> 01:35:30,919
An act of madness, more like that.

891
01:35:30,967 --> 01:35:34,880
What would you call a woman, who 
lives her family without a reason?

892
01:35:34,967 --> 01:35:39,404
- That's not true!
- To appeal to atternal love

893
01:35:39,447 --> 01:35:42,644
geraniums are ideal. 
The're over there.

894
01:35:42,687 --> 01:35:46,885
If they're not enough I have 
more out in the back.

895
01:35:50,647 --> 01:35:53,639
Your son Nic takes drugs.

896
01:35:53,687 --> 01:35:55,439
Shit!

897
01:36:07,047 --> 01:36:10,039
"I'm an unworthy mother.

898
01:36:10,087 --> 01:36:14,080
I'm going back to my family 
and my obligations.

899
01:36:14,127 --> 01:36:18,245
My warmest thanks for everything 
you've done for me.

900
01:36:20,167 --> 01:36:23,239
Good bye. Rosalba."

902
01:36:36,487 --> 01:36:38,637
Hello!

904
01:36:52,487 --> 01:36:54,079
Mom!

905
01:36:54,127 --> 01:36:57,119
Nic! Hello!

906
01:36:57,167 --> 01:36:59,317
Why is everything so neat?

907
01:36:59,367 --> 01:37:03,360
- It was dad.
- On his own?

908
01:37:03,407 --> 01:37:07,525
No, he called "Splendor".
It took them two days.

909
01:37:07,567 --> 01:37:10,559
Your vacation is over?

910
01:37:10,607 --> 01:37:13,280
Yes, it is.

911
01:37:16,287 --> 01:37:19,324
Is it true, that you take drugs?

912
01:37:19,367 --> 01:37:23,679
- Who told you?
- Aunt Ketty.

913
01:37:24,287 --> 01:37:27,518
Mom, joints aren't drugs.

914
01:37:27,567 --> 01:37:31,276
- So what are they?
- Joints.

915
01:37:34,127 --> 01:37:37,244
Pour me a glass.

916
01:37:39,087 --> 01:37:43,603
Now all the people who own Freon 
ones have to ditch them.

917
01:37:43,647 --> 01:37:46,115
The same goes for fluorocarbon.

918
01:37:46,167 --> 01:37:50,399
They have to buy conditioners,
with that other new Gas...

919
01:37:50,447 --> 01:37:53,405
- With HRC.
- Right!

920
01:37:53,447 --> 01:37:57,884
The standartized ecological conditioner.
Fortunately heat doesn't bother me.

921
01:37:58,087 --> 01:38:02,399
You're kidding! Last year on the 
beach you haven't stopped the fan.

922
01:38:04,247 --> 01:38:06,203
Very funny...

923
01:38:06,247 --> 01:38:10,240
Did you show mom, what your 
Italian teacher wrote?

924
01:38:10,687 --> 01:38:15,158
- Go ahead.
- What's happened?

925
01:38:15,247 --> 01:38:19,160
- I'm paying for private lessons...
- Need your car tonight?

926
01:38:19,287 --> 01:38:23,280
- Where are you going?
- There's a new club opening.

927
01:38:23,327 --> 01:38:27,320
Cinzia's cousin runs the bar.
We can drink for free.

928
01:38:27,367 --> 01:38:31,326
Can't he pump gas instead?
You always empty the tank. 

929
01:38:31,367 --> 01:38:35,360
They siphon it out with a tube.
Stop hanging out with those misfits.

930
01:38:35,407 --> 01:38:39,400
What's this about the tube?

931
01:38:39,447 --> 01:38:42,484
Nothing, Papa. Forget it.

932
01:38:58,887 --> 01:39:03,165
- Mimmo, I wanted to tell you...
- Alba, listen.

933
01:39:03,567 --> 01:39:07,276
As far as I'm concerned,
nothing happened.

937
01:40:01,927 --> 01:40:06,876
Grazia asks, if you'd like to eat
with us. We've ordered from Chinese.

938
01:40:15,007 --> 01:40:19,683
Fernando, pull yourself together.
You can't spend the whole day moping.

939
01:40:20,607 --> 01:40:25,078
It happens to be my day off.

940
01:40:27,727 --> 01:40:32,084
- Yes, but not a day of fasting.
- Sorry, I'm not hungry at all.

942
01:40:52,407 --> 01:40:56,878
How about a quick game of 
darts then, Fernando?

943
01:40:59,807 --> 01:41:03,720
- Grandpa, what's bothering you?
- Nothing, Eliseo.

944
01:41:03,767 --> 01:41:08,283
"Your words sound obscure, but
one day I'll understand."

945
01:41:08,327 --> 01:41:12,286
- You always say that.
- I'm bothered by my own folly.

946
01:41:12,327 --> 01:41:16,684
Once again happiness knocked 
on my door in vain.

947
01:41:18,967 --> 01:41:22,676
Why didn't you answer?

948
01:41:23,327 --> 01:41:27,286
I was deaf and now I languish.

950
01:42:16,967 --> 01:42:20,880
It's a mistake! Andrea, please,
give me permission to see him!

951
01:42:20,967 --> 01:42:23,959
- Try to forget him
- I can't and I won't.

952
01:42:24,007 --> 01:42:28,080
Juan's my husband.
What if he weren't?

953
01:42:28,887 --> 01:42:32,482
What do you mean?
He is my husband!

954
01:42:32,527 --> 01:42:34,882
Don't ask me to help him.

955
01:42:43,967 --> 01:42:46,959
I wanted to kill him...

956
01:42:47,007 --> 01:42:50,966
Rosalba! Have you forgotten us?

957
01:42:51,607 --> 01:42:55,600
- No.
- When will you be back?

958
01:42:56,287 --> 01:42:59,962
My life is here.

959
01:43:04,647 --> 01:43:08,083
Fernando, Rosalba is
waiting for you.

960
01:43:09,287 --> 01:43:12,359
What engenders such certainty?

961
01:43:12,407 --> 01:43:15,399
My female intuition.

964
01:43:59,527 --> 01:44:03,076
You are Fermo.

965
01:44:03,367 --> 01:44:06,359
And you're Narcissus.

966
01:44:06,407 --> 01:44:09,285
Fernando Girasol.

967
01:44:09,327 --> 01:44:13,764
I'm the owner of the accordion
Mrs. Rosalba played.

968
01:44:13,807 --> 01:44:17,766
I realized that.
Have you brought me news?

969
01:44:17,807 --> 01:44:21,277
I've brought the instrument 
as a pledge. In return

970
01:44:21,327 --> 01:44:25,718
I'd like to ask you for your van.
I know you possess an exemplar

971
01:44:25,767 --> 01:44:29,965
for deliveries to a company 
on the mainland.

972
01:44:30,567 --> 01:44:33,604
Get to the point.

973
01:44:33,647 --> 01:44:38,277
I intend to descend to the Abruzzi
and bring Rosalba back here.

974
01:44:38,647 --> 01:44:42,959
Two companions are joining 
me on this quest.

975
01:44:48,287 --> 01:44:52,280
It hasn't seen a freeway in 20 years.
Change the oil, pump up the tires...

976
01:44:52,327 --> 01:44:54,921
and respect its age.

978
01:45:15,847 --> 01:45:19,044
But... why are you here?

979
01:45:19,087 --> 01:45:22,204
I want to quit school.

980
01:45:22,247 --> 01:45:25,284
What is this idea?

981
01:45:25,327 --> 01:45:28,285
It's not an idea. Everything sucks.

982
01:45:28,327 --> 01:45:31,637
So, everything sucks?

983
01:45:31,687 --> 01:45:35,999
You know I stopped studying
and went to work for your uncle?

984
01:45:36,047 --> 01:45:40,040
- And?
- I regret it now.

985
01:45:40,287 --> 01:45:44,280
You all say that.

986
01:45:45,367 --> 01:45:49,042
Come to the supermarket with me.

987
01:45:49,087 --> 01:45:52,921
You know "Orlando Furioso"?

988
01:45:53,007 --> 01:45:57,205
The guy who hoes nuts and his
brain blasts over the moon?

989
01:45:57,247 --> 01:46:00,284
It's not quite like that.

990
01:46:00,327 --> 01:46:04,400
- What would you like to do now?
- I don't know.

991
01:46:04,447 --> 01:46:07,996
What? There must be something
you like.

992
01:46:08,047 --> 01:46:12,120
- How many people do what they like?
- Your father does.

993
01:46:12,167 --> 01:46:16,240
Can you see me selling toilets 
and windows for the next 40 years?

994
01:46:37,287 --> 01:46:41,963
Rosalba. Since you went 
life is a pain.

995
01:46:42,007 --> 01:46:46,000
The nights are torment,
the days are harsh.

996
01:46:46,047 --> 01:46:50,723
If I've made this journey then 
for one reason 'tis owed.

997
01:46:50,767 --> 01:46:54,760
That you'll return to 
light up my abode.

998
01:46:54,807 --> 01:46:56,798
Fernando.

999
01:46:56,847 --> 01:47:00,806
What a surprise. You take me unaware.

1000
01:47:00,847 --> 01:47:04,806
You're busy with your buys 
and caught up in your cares.

1001
01:47:09,767 --> 01:47:13,806
This is my son Nicola.
And... this is Mr. Fernando.

1002
01:47:14,287 --> 01:47:18,405
I realize, that the situation 
may seem bizarre for you.

1003
01:47:18,447 --> 01:47:22,440
Nevertheless I've come to 
lay claim to your mother.

1004
01:47:22,487 --> 01:47:24,762
Abd why?

1005
01:47:24,807 --> 01:47:26,923
Because...

1006
01:47:26,967 --> 01:47:29,606
I love her.

1008
01:47:44,407 --> 01:47:48,195
Soul of my sorrowful life

1009
01:47:48,247 --> 01:47:52,240
beneath this colorless sky.

1010
01:47:52,487 --> 01:47:56,082
Let me live in peace

1011
01:47:56,127 --> 01:48:00,245
without bitterness or pain.

1012
01:48:00,367 --> 01:48:04,042
Far from my emotions

1013
01:48:04,087 --> 01:48:08,239
I wish only to sleep.

1014
01:48:08,407 --> 01:48:12,366
A nest of peaceful silence,

1015
01:48:12,407 --> 01:48:16,446
is my natural refuge.

1016
01:48:16,487 --> 01:48:20,275
The look in your eyes makes
me tremble,

1017
01:48:20,327 --> 01:48:24,115
the lost voice of your heart,

1018
01:48:24,167 --> 01:48:28,046
is a defeat of all my illusions.

1019
01:48:28,087 --> 01:48:32,126
The fresh dew on jasmine.

1020
01:48:32,567 --> 01:48:36,355
Your lips as sweet as honey.

1021
01:48:36,407 --> 01:48:39,683
Pink like roses, carminred
like carnation.

1022
01:48:40,167 --> 01:48:43,239
For you I return to my dreams,

1023
01:48:43,927 --> 01:48:47,078
I won't hide anymore.

1024
01:48:48,527 --> 01:48:51,087
May I have this dance, Mrs.?

1026
01:49:17,927 --> 01:49:20,839
I don't wish to seem impetuous

1027
01:49:20,887 --> 01:49:24,084
but can't we drop "Mr. and Mrs."?


